<!--BEGIN CONTENT-->

<P><FONT color="red">19th March 99:</FONT> The account suspension period
has been increased from 30 days to 90 days. This means that they will
now only suspend your account after 90 days of inactivity instead of the
previous 30 days. Effective from the 15th March 1999.</P>

<P><FONT color="red">1st feb. 99:</FONT> Customer support phone charge
dropped from &#163;1 per minute to 50p a minute (not that it's much use
for us Amiga owners... :-/ ). Effective from the 1st Feb. 1999.</P>

<P><FONT color="red">20th Jan. 99:</FONT> To reduce abuse of Freeserve's
services (from SPAM, etc.), they require that from the 18th January
1999, you must release your phone number when logging in.</P>

<P>This means that if you currently with-hold your number using 141, you
will only be able to fetch mail, news and browse the web. If you
currently do not with hold your number, you don't need to do anything
else.</P>

<P><FONT color="red">31th Dec. 98:</FONT>Re-designed and moved site onto
Freeserve's server. It also appears that you can now apply for another
account from your existing account on Freeserve.</P>

<!--END CONTENT-->
